subSubSection.paragraph:
The species is only moderately euryhaline, tolerating 26–36ppt salinity (

Flores
1973b

). Heat coma temperatures are amongst the highest for Caribbean littorinids, in the range 46.9–47°C (
Britton 1992
; 
McMahon 2001
; for alternative measures of temperature tolerance see 
Fraenkel 1968
, and 

Mahieu 
et al
. 1987

), which exceeds recorded rock surface temperatures (
Minton & Gochfeld 2001
). Individuals survive emersion for between one and seven months (
Mattox 1949
; 
Yipp & Carefoot 1988
; 
Britton 1992
).
